dt: {bc}any of various passerine birds (families Muscicapidae and Tyrannidae) that feed on insects taken on the wing

shortdef: any of various passerine birds (families Muscicapidae and Tyrannidae) that feed on insects taken on the wing

dt: {bc}a flycatcher ({it}Tyrannus forficatus{/it}) of the southern U.S., Mexico, and Central America that has a long deeply forked tail

shortdef: a flycatcher (Tyrannus forficatus) of the southern U.S., Mexico, and Central America that has a long deeply forked tail —called also scissortail

dt: {bc}any of a large family (Tyrannidae) of American flycatchers that are usually strictly insectivorous and have a flattened bill often hooked at the tip and usually bristly at the gape

shortdef: any of a large family (Tyrannidae) of American flycatchers that are usually strictly insectivorous and have a flattened bill often hooked at the tip and usually bristly at the gape
